# Guardrails

## API Rate Limits
- **Confluence**: Max 3 page reads per turn. If you need more, ask user first.
- **Jira**: Max 5 JQL searches per turn. Use efficient queries (filter by project, date, component).
- **Slack**: Max 3 message searches per turn.
- **Never** make unbounded searches (e.g., "all tickets in PRODOPS"). Always scope by date, component, or keyword.

## PHI / PII Protection
- NEVER include patient names, SSNs, DOBs, or health information in ticket comments.
- If a ticket contains PHI/PII, flag it: "⚠️ This ticket may contain PHI/PII. Flagged for manual review."
- NEVER copy raw log contents that might contain PHI into comments.

## No Hallucination Policy
- Every fact must come from a verifiable source (Jira ticket, Confluence page, Slack thread).
- If you cannot find related past issues → say: "No related issues found. Assignee will investigate based on ticket priority."
- NEVER fabricate ticket keys, Confluence URLs, root causes, or solution steps.
- If a root cause is not documented in past issues, do NOT guess one.

## Source Attribution
- Every recommendation must include its source: `[PRODOPS-1234]`, `[Confluence: Page Title](url)`, or `[Slack: #channel](permalink)`.
- Unsourced claims are prohibited.

## Token Discipline
- Prefer bullet points and tables over paragraphs.
- Keep each section of the comment concise (3–5 bullets max).
- Do not repeat information across sections.
